Teo emulator originally written by: Gilles Fetis, Eric Botcazou, Alexandre Pukall, 
                                    Francois Mouret, Samuel Devulder

Teo-ng a continuation of teo, started by Samuel Cuella, brings improvements such as:
-Allegro(which provides joystick supprot) on Linux instead of X11 only. 
-SDL2 port for Linux and Win32
-Original Xbox port using SDL2 and nxdk
-Gettext instead of static strings for all platforms, including MS-DOS
-Autotools-enabled build system which supports cross-compiling from Linux
 to MS-DOS (DJGPP) and Win32(mingw)
